## Summary

`ProxyCacheWarmer::warmUp()` uses `scandir()` to collect generated proxy files **without filtering by extension**, causing it to return temporary files left by `doctrine/orm`'s atomic write mechanism. Symfony 7.4's strict `CacheWarmerAggregate` validation then throws an exception.

## Environment

- symfony/doctrine-bridge: 7.4.x (latest)
- doctrine/orm: 2.20+ / 2.21.x-dev / 3.2.x
- PHP: 8.2+

## Bug details

**In `doctrine/orm`'s `ProxyFactory`, proxy files are written atomically:**

```php
// vendor/doctrine/orm/src/Proxy/ProxyFactory.php
$tmpFileName = $fileName . '.' . bin2hex(random_bytes(12));
file_put_contents($tmpFileName, $proxyCode);
@chmod($tmpFileName, 0664);
rename($tmpFileName, $fileName);  // rename is not checked for errors
```

This means files like `__CG__SomeEntity.php.2eb37f8174836c6595d337b3` exist in the proxy directory during generation (and can persist if `rename()` fails silently).

**Meanwhile, `ProxyCacheWarmer::warmUp()` scans everything:**

```php
// src/Symfony/Bridge/Doctrine/CacheWarmer/ProxyCacheWarmer.php
$em->getProxyFactory()->generateProxyClasses($classes);

foreach (scandir($proxyCacheDir) as $file) {
    if (!is_dir($file = $proxyCacheDir.'/'.$file)) {
        $files[] = $file;  // includes .php.{hash} temp files!
    }
}
```

**Result — Symfony 7.4 `CacheWarmerAggregate` throws:**

```
"Symfony\Bridge\Doctrine\CacheWarmer\ProxyCacheWarmer::warmUp()" should return a list
of files or classes but "/var/cache/prod/doctrine/orm/Proxies/__CG__SomeEntity.php.2eb37f8174836c6595d337b3"
is none of them.
```

## Why it's intermittent

- Fresh deploy to clean cache → `rename()` finishes before anything else reads the dir → ✅ OK
- Concurrent PHP workers (e.g. php-fpm pool) warming up simultaneously → race: `scandir()` in one worker catches the temp file another worker is writing → ❌ FAIL
- `rename()` fails silently (disk pressure, NFS, etc.) → temp file persists → every subsequent warmup fails → ❌ FAIL

## Proposed fix

One-line change to filter `scandir()` to only `.php` files:

```diff
  foreach (scandir($proxyCacheDir) as $file) {
-     if (!is_dir($file = $proxyCacheDir.'/'.$file)) {
+     if (!is_dir($file = $proxyCacheDir.'/'.$file) && str_ends_with($file, '.php')) {
          $files[] = $file;
      }
  }
```

This makes the warmer robust against:
- Temp files from the atomic write
- Any other non-PHP files that may appear in the proxy directory

## Notes

The fix should live in `src/Symfony/Bridge/Doctrine/CacheWarmer/ProxyCacheWarmer.php`. The same guard could optionally be added inside `doctrine/orm`'s `ProxyFactory` to verify `rename()` succeeded, but filtering on the consumer side is sufficient.

Confirmed present in the latest commit on the 7.4 branch.

### Symfony version(s) affected

8.1.1

### Description

Object mapper seems to have a problem when creating  with this configuration.

`new ObjectMapper(propertyAccessor: new PropertyAccessor(throw: PropertyAccessor::DO_NOT_THROW));`

As per the example transform function (**transformProperty**). should receive the string value of $sourceProperty (**ABC**), instead it will throw an error saying

> Target::transformProperty(): Argument #1 ($value) must be of type string, null given

This worked well in **object-mapper:8.1.0**

### How to reproduce

```
class Source
{
    public string $id = '123';
    public string $sourceProperty = 'ABC';
}

#[Map(source: Source::class)]
class Target
{
    #[Map(source: 'sourceProperty', transform: [self::class, 'transformProperty'])]
    public string $targetProperty;

    public static function transformProperty(string $value): string
    {
        return $value;
    }
}

$mapper = new ObjectMapper(propertyAccessor: new PropertyAccessor(throw: PropertyAccessor::DO_NOT_THROW));
$mapper->map(new Source(), Target::class);
```

